dk.dibs.android.library
Interface PaymentResultListener

public interface PaymentResultListener

Client apps implement this to receive notifications from ongoing payment processing.

See Also:
DibsPayment.setPaymentResultListener(PaymentResultListener)

Field Detail

CRITICAL_ERROR_MAX

static final int CRITICAL_ERROR_MAX
Error numbers below this constant are considered critical.

When handling errors in errorOccurred(Map) you should use this constant to determine if the error is critical, in which case payment processing must be stopped.

paymentCancelled

void paymentCancelled(Map<String,String> paymentData)
Called from payment window, following a call to DibsPayment.cancelPayment(), when the payment window is done with its cancel processing.

If a cancel URL is loaded as part of cancel processing, both cancelUrlLoaded() and this method is called.

Parameters:
paymentData - the payment data from the payment window

errorOccurred

void errorOccurred(Map<String,String> errorInfo)
Called from payment window, when some error occurs.

You should use this to taker proper action in showing or logging errors and maybe closing the payment window. The parameters will include two keys ERROR_INFO_KEY_NUMBER and ERROR_INFO_KEY_MESSAGE, describing a code and a message for the error. IMPORTANT NOTE: Error codes <= CRITICAL_ERROR_MAX indicate critical errors. Your app SHOULD close the payment window in these cases and ensure that the payment does not continue.

Parameters:
errorInfo - information about the error that occurred.
